This paper is about end-to-end speech to text translation using deep learning, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and speech processing. The paper also discusses the usage of pre-trained models, which falls under the category of transfer learning, and can be categorized under cs.SD (Sound), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also discusses the impact of different loss functions on the performance, which can be categorized under cs.SD.
